"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"6778fc",
"children":[
"Vasculitis is an inflammation of blood vessels that causes stenosis or attenuation with subsequent tissue ischemia, aneurysms, or hemorrhage. This condition may be secondary to an underlying process or occur as a primary disease. Primary vasculitides may be categorized based on the size of the blood vessel that is predominantly involved, the pattern of organ involvement, and the histopathology."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_rm_s15_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"49157a",
"children":[
"Aortic aneurysm and aortic dissection are potential complications of giant cell arteritis; aortic dissection may occur with or without preceding aneurysm formation."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9e5f23",
"children":[
"Polyarteritis nodosa kidney disease does not involve the glomerulus (no urine erythrocyte casts, but hematuria or proteinuria may occur)."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0ecceb",
"children":[
"Do not make a diagnosis of eosinophilic granulomatosis with polyangiitis in the absence of eosinophilia."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
