"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose giant cell arteritis. For management, select immediate prednisone plus tocilizumab and arrange for temporal artery biopsy within 2 weeks."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"42581e",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 32-year-old woman has a 6-month history of fever, myalgia, arthralgia, and weight loss. Two days ago, she developed achy pain in her arms when working with her arms above her head."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
